   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Operate the lift, tilt and attachment controls. Listen for
unusual noises. These may indicate a need for repair.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Check for loose bolts and nuts on the carriage. Remove any
debris from the carriage and mast.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Check the forks and attachments for free operation and damage. Have repairs made if
          necessary.</p>
            <p>
               <fig id="fig_yrw_fxz_5gc">
                  <image href="media/image1140.png"
                         id="image_asw_fxz_5gc"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
               <p>Typical Example</p>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Brush a film of oil on all links of the chain.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Raise and lower the carriage a few times to allow lubricant to enter into the chain
          links.</p>
            <p>
               <note type="warning">
                  <p>Lubricate chains more frequently than normal in applications where the lift truck is
            operating in an atmosphere which could cause corrosion of components or when lift truck
            must work in rapid lift cycles.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Check the air cleaner housing for loose latches.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
